Dear Dr. Goodwin or others:

I am a beginner for C++/cantera.  I managed to install cantera from 
source sucessfully.  The examples for Python work well. However, 
when I tried to follow the instruction for C++. It can't compile 
even for the simplest example.  Then after changing the head file to 
its specific directory (include "c:\..."), it sucessfully compiled. 
However, yield many errors when building the exe file. One example 
error is 

"error LNK2001: unresolved external symbol "public: void __thiscall 
Cantera::ThermoPhase::setState_TPX(double,double,class 
std::basic_string<char,struct std::char_traits<char>,class 
std::allocator<char> > const &)" (?setState_TPX@Ther
moPhase@Cantera@@QAEXNNABV?$basic_string@DU?$char_traits@D@std@@V?
$allocator@D@2@@std@@@Z)"

Could you please help me with this issue?

Thanks,
Joe
